Ad Text:
Initial 6-month contract (high likelihood of extension)
Sydney – Onsite
Long-term program of work
 
About the Role
 
We are seeking an experienced Infrastructure Engineer to support a major data centre and virtualisation program. This role will oversee core infrastructure operations, delivery, and optimisation across compute, storage, virtualisation, and data centre technologies, with a strong emphasis on enterprise storage platforms such as Hitachi, Dell EMC, and NetApp. In addition to technical leadership, the position requires proven people management capability, guiding junior engineers and coordinating tasks across cross-functional teams.
 
The successful candidate will play a key part in stabilising, enhancing, and modernising infrastructure services while ensuring high availability, reliability, and performance across all environments.
 
Responsibilities
 

Oversee day-to-day operations of data centre infrastructure, including compute, storage, and virtualisation platforms.
Manage and support enterprise storage technologies including Hitachi (HCP, VSP, HNAS), Dell EMC, NetApp, and other SAN/NAS platforms.
Administer and optimise VMware vSphere, vCenter, ESXi clusters, and related virtualisation ecosystems.
Lead incident management, problem resolution, root-cause analysis, capacity management, and performance optimisation
Deliver infrastructure upgrades, migrations, patching, and lifecycle management activities.
Provide mentoring, task allocation, and technical leadership to junior team members.
Work closely with project teams on data centre modernisation, consolidation, and refresh initiatives.
Monitor infrastructure availability, storage utilisation, and performance using standard enterprise toolsets.
Collaborate with network, cyber, and application teams to ensure alignment and smooth delivery of cross-functional initiatives.
Maintain documentation including LLDs/HLDs, runbooks, configuration baselines, and operational procedures.
Support continuous improvement activities to uplift stability, resilience, and operational maturity.
 
 
Requirements
 

Strong experience working in enterprise data centre environments, including compute, storage, and virtualisation operations.
Comprehensive hands-on experience with Hitachi Storage (VSP, HCP, HNAS), and working knowledge of Dell EMC, NetApp, and other enterprise SAN/NAS platforms.
Solid background in VMware vSphere, ESXi, vCenter, SRM, and virtualisation best practices.
Strong understanding of backup and replication technologies (e.g., Veeam, Data Domain, RecoverPoint, HUR).
Experience with infrastructure automation tools (PowerShell, Ansible, PowerCLI) highly regarded.
Demonstrated ability to manage and mentor team members, including workload coordination and performance support.
Clear understanding of ITIL processes: incident, problem, change, and configuration management.
Strong troubleshooting capabilities across compute, storage, and virtualisation stacks.
Ability to work effectively onsite, engaging with stakeholders, project teams, and operations.
Excellent documentation skills and ability to communicate complex technical issues clearly.
 
Desired Qualifications
 

Vendor certifications in Hitachi (HDS), Dell EMC, NetApp, or VMware (VCP) are highly advantageous.
Experience in hybrid cloud environments (Azure/AWS) is a plus.
Exposure to data centre migration or modernisation programs.
ITIL Foundation certification.
 
How To Apply:
If you understand and meet the above requirements please click APPLY or please contact Liz – lizc@greenlightworldwide.com or call 0482 072 644 for further information.

Job Description


The Data Science & AI team develops, builds, and delivers production-grade AI products to provide solutions to business problems. Key responsibilities include architecting scalable software, building agentic workflows, and managing the ops and pipelines used to deploy them. We push the envelope in what is possible and work on new and novel implementations of AI engineering.
 
Areas of focus for the team include leveraging LLMs to assist our content creation stakeholders, architecting enterprise-grade semantic search engines, and building agentic workflows that transform raw data into actionable business operations.


Day to day you will:

Architect, maintain and deploy scalable and robust production-grade AI applications and microservices.
Champion utilising non-deterministic flows to drive measurable business outcomes.
Design advanced retrieval architectures (RAG) and optimise LLM orchestration for latency and cost.
Build robust APIs to integrate AI agents with internal databases and third-party tools.
Evaluate agent's performance using evaluations and tests to iterate on prompts, agent tools and agents orchestration to improve output quality and reliability.
Manage the observability and logging of deployed agents to proactively identify and resolve edge cases.
Champion engineering best practices and stay ahead of the rapidly evolving GenAI landscape.

Qualifications


What you’ll bring:

Strong programming skills in Python with a recent focus on building scalable production grade AI applications.
Proven experience with orchestration frameworks (ADK preferred) and implementing RAG architectures with Vector Databases.
Understanding of software design, service architecture, and best practices for scalable systems.
A proven track record of prior production-grade projects utilising prompt engineering & system design with considerations for latency and user experience.
Bonus
Master's degree in Computer Science or AI.
Deep understanding of foundational models and fine-tuning techniques.
Knowledge of evaluation frameworks (e.g., RAGAS, TruLens) or "LLM-as-a-judge" patterns.
Familiarity with Google Cloud Platform (Vertex AI) and containerisation (Docker/Kubernetes).

More info at Nine Careers.

Job Title: AI Factory / HPA Technical Solutions Architect (Australia)
Ad Text:
Why WWT?

At World Wide Technology, we work together to make a new world happen. Our important work benefits our clients and partners as much as it does our people and communities across the globe. WWT is dedicated to achieving its mission of creating a profitable growth company that is also a Great Place to Work for All. We achieve this through our world-class culture, generous benefits and by delivering cutting-edge technology solutions for our clients.

Founded in 1990, World Wide Technology (WWT) is a global technology solutions provider leading the AI and Digital Revolution. With more than $20 billion in annual revenue, WWT combines the power of strategy, execution and partnership to accelerate digital transformational outcomes for large public and private organizations. Through its Advanced Technology Center, a collaborative ecosystem of the world's most advanced hardware and software solutions, WWT helps clients and partners conceptualize, test and validate innovative technology solutions for the best business outcomes and then deploys them at scale through its global warehousing, distribution and integration capabilities.

With over 10,000 employees and more than 55 locations around the world, WWT's culture, built on a set of core values and established leadership philosophies, has been recognized 13 years in a row by Fortune and Great Place to Work® for its unique blend of determination, innovation and creating a great place to work for all. Want to work with highly motivated individuals on high-performance teams? Join WWT today!

(High-Performance Computing, Networking, and Storage supporting, Artificial Intelligence, and Machine Learning). This role will include assisting customers with the adoption and sizing of GPU hardware as well as building and deploying GPU-accelerated technologies.

Identify and drive new business opportunities with the WWT field organization.

A strong understand of AI workload management and tools like Aarna, Apolo, Rafay, ClearML, and others including the NVIDIA software suite

Collaborate and align with our professional services organization to set the strategy for growing our HPA and AI services business

Participate in regular virtual team meetings and training related to HPA and AI Factory products and solutions.

Support business development and marketing initiatives as needed.

Achieve OEM certification requirements to maintain partner status across HPA

Develop partner ecosystems and relationships complementary to WWT's go-to-market strategy where applicable.

Drive partner product announcements, software updates, and product roadmaps. Assist in developing a go-to-market strategy for WWT to grow the AI & HPA business.

Work with internal collaborators including adjacent practices, partner management, sales operations, and marketing to accelerate data strategy business.

 

Qualifications:

At least 5 years selling, architecting, implementing, and/or marketing compute solutions, including the following solutions areas and products:

Supporting strategic sales initiatives.

Accelerated, Edge, and High-Performance Computing platforms from NVIDIA, AMD, Intel, Dell, and HPE, including blade, rack-mount, and modular solutions.

Working with our storage experts and networking experts and a working knowledge of how AI impacts all components of the stack

Understanding AI workload orchestration and MLOps concepts needed to bring AI Infrastructure to the Data Science groups that will consume them.

Interfacing, creating, and fostering relationships with strategic partners including NVIDIA, AMD, Intel, and all OEMs that support the latest accelerators (HPE, Dell, SuperMicro, and Others)

Acceleration technologies such as GPUs, DPUs, and FPGAs

OS and virtualization technologies:

DGX OS (based on Ubuntu)

Openshift AI Platform

NVIDIA NVAIE, Mission Control, Dynamo, NIM, Blueprints, Run:ai and entire ecosystem.

AI workload management and orchestration tools

Made possible with extensive research, testing and vertically integrated manufacturing, the company has progressed into deep technology fields, including robotics, inertial, photonic and quantum sensing, artificial intelligence, underwater acoustics, and GPS antennas and receivers. Petraeus (US Army, Ret.), Advanced Navigation supports AUKUS by collaborating with UK and US partners to drive innovation, fortify supply chains, and enhance allied resilience and interoperability in defense. #JoinTheAutonomyRevolution




About the role

In this role you will be a subject matter expert, filling a critical knowledge gap in your engineering team. Given that our company heavily relies on software to enhance hardware performance, this person must have a strong multidisciplinary background across physics, electronics, and software.

The ideal candidate would have a unique blend of hands-on testing experience and a deep theoretical understanding of sensor technologies. Your background should bridge the gap between our software, mechanical, and electronic engineering teams.


What you'll do

Contribute to the research and development of novel, internally-developed sensor technologies.

Provide expert guidance to the engineering team on the critical properties of sensors for inertial navigation systems.

Develop and implement advanced sensor calibration techniques to optimise system performance.

Lead the testing, characterisation, and selection of third-party inertial sensors.

Analyse test data to identify sensor performance limitations and areas for improvement.

Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate sensors into our diverse product range, from low-cost to high-end systems.

Qualifications

Sensor Testing and Characterisation: They must have proven experience in designing and executing tests for inertial sensors (accelerometers and gyroscopes). This includes understanding test methodologies, sources of error, and how to analyse the resulting data.

Sensor Development: Experience in the development of new sensors is crucial. This could involve technologies like MEMS (Micro-Electro-Mechanical Systems), FOG (Fibre-Optic Gyroscopes), or other emerging sensor tech. This experience ensures they can contribute to your in-house sensor development.

Inertial Navigation Systems (INS) Expertise: A deep understanding of how sensor characteristics impact the performance of an INS is paramount. They should be able to identify which sensor properties are most critical for your high-performance navigation systems.

Calibration Techniques: The candidate should be proficient in advanced sensor calibration methods to minimise errors and optimise performance.

Software and Data Analysis Skills: Proficiency in software tools used for data acquisition and analysis, such as Python or MATLAB, is important.
Industry Experience: While not mandatory, experience in one of our key industries—like defense, maritime, or autonomous vehicles—would be a significant plus

Educational Background: A degree in a relevant field such as Physics, Mechatronics, Electrical Engineering, or a closely related discipline is essential. An advanced degree (Master's or PhD) would be highly advantageous, especially if their research was focused on sensor technology or inertial navigation. Australian citizens are desirable for security reasons, ADF experience is highly regarded and Veterans are encouraged to apply

Viva Leisure have the mission of connecting health and wellness to as many people as possible through our range of awesome, affordable and accessible facilities.  Our vision is to be the #1 in the industry for our employees, our shareholders, our franchisees, our communities, and of course our members.

As the founding Senior Data Engineer for Viva 360, you’ll design and build the data and AI backbone of Viva Leisure’s new analytics platform. This hands-on role focuses on developing scalable data pipelines, machine learning infrastructure, and decision engines that transform raw data into real-time, predictive insights driving member retention, acquisition, and personalisation.

You’ll architect and operationalise production-grade systems, implement data governance, and integrate ML models into core business functions. This is a rare opportunity to shape the future of data and AI in the fitness industry — with autonomy to make key technical decisions, direct visibility to leadership, and the chance to expand the platform’s impact across brands and use cases.

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES 

ML Pipeline Engineering (40%)

Design and deliver production-grade ML pipelines to support churn prediction and member acquisition models.
Develop and maintain feature stores for reusable member attributes across multiple use cases.
Build model training, versioning, and deployment workflows using MLflow and other MLOps tools.
Create and manage model serving endpoints to enable real-time inference at scale.
Engineer decision engine pipelines that automate marketing interventions and member engagement.
Design rule-based and ML-driven decisioning workflows to optimise business outcomes.

Data Infrastructure (35%)

Build scalable ETL/ELT pipelines ingesting data from 500+ locations and multiple external platforms.
Implement Databricks lakehouse architecture with Delta Lake for unified storage and processing.
Configure and optimise cloud compute resources for both batch and streaming data workloads.
Design data models optimised for analytics, reporting, and ML feature extraction.

Data Quality & Governance (15%)

Implement Unity Catalog governance with fine-grained (row-level) security across 11 brands.
Build automated data quality checks and validation processes into pipelines.
Develop audit trails and lineage tracking for compliance with member PII regulations.
Manage schema evolution and ensure resilience for downstream consumers.

Operations & Optimisation (10%)

Monitor pipeline performance, ML model inference latency, and overall system reliability.
Automate workflows using orchestration tools such as Airflow or Data Factory.
Establish robust alerting frameworks for data freshness, pipeline failures, and model performance degradation.
Maintain clear documentation of architecture, pipelines, workflows, and runbooks to ensure knowledge continuity.
SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE 

We are looking for someone with:

Education and Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Data Engineering, or related field (or equivalent experience).
Postgraduate qualifications in data engineering, data science, or cloud technologies desirable.
Professional certifications in AWS, Azure, or GCP (Data Engineer focus) highly regarded.

Skills and Experience

7+ years’ experience building and maintaining production-grade data platforms and ML pipelines.
Expert in Python (PySpark, pandas) and SQL for data engineering, modelling, and optimisation.
Proven experience with cloud-based data services (AWS, Azure, or GCP).
Skilled in designing data lakehouse architectures, governance frameworks, and scalable ETL/ELT workflows (Airflow, Data Factory, etc.).
Strong understanding of dimensional modelling and ML lifecycle management, including deployment, versioning, and monitoring.
Proficient with Git for version control and collaborative development.
Familiarity with MLflow, Kafka/Kinesis/Event Hubs, and BI tools (Power BI, Tableau, Looker) desirable.
Experience working in multi-tenant, regulated data environments handling PII and compliance requirements.
Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills, with a proactive, ownership-driven mindset.
Bonus: Experience in fitness, leisure, or subscription-based industries, and knowledge of Australian data privacy standards.

ABOUT VIVA LEISURE

At Viva Leisure, our mission is simple: to connect health and wellness to as many people as possible through our awesome, affordable, and accessible facilities. Our vision is to be the number one in the industry — benefitting our members, shareholders, franchisees, communities, and employees alike.

As an Australian-owned and ASX-listed company, we offer a diverse range of health and fitness solutions, including big-box health clubs, express gyms, high-intensity group training studios, Pilates, yoga, aquatics, women’s-only facilities, personal training, and more. Established in 2004, our key brands include Club Lime, hiit republic, Plus Fitness, GROUNDUP, and Rebalance. With over 300 facilities across Australia and internationally, including corporate-owned and franchised sites, we’re proud to serve diverse communities.

In 2020, Viva Leisure acquired Chain Collective Group to expand our fitness franchise brands both domestically and internationally. Chain Collective now operates as the franchising arm of Viva Leisure, proudly holding Plus Fitness as its flagship franchised brand — paving the way for the continued growth and success of multiple fitness concepts across Australia and beyond.

In 2024, Viva Leisure acquired a 34% stake in Boutique Fitness Studios (BFS), the master franchisee for leading global brands including Club Pilates, Rumble Boxing, StretchLab, and CycleBar. This partnership marks an exciting new chapter as Viva’s Rebalance Pilates & Yoga studios transition to Club Pilates, uniting local expertise with world-class brand standards to deliver a premium member experience. That same year, Viva Leisure also acquired a 25% equity stake in World Gym Australia, along with three corporate-owned World Gym locations in Queensland — Stafford, Coomera, and Underwood — further strengthening our presence in the premium fitness sector.
